obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (32228)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32228&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Export-Import Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1981.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 1st January 1982, vide notification No. S.O. 919(E), dated 29th December, 1981 (except section 26), see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `1st March 1982, vide notification No. S.O. 91(E), dated 23rd February, 1982 (in respect of section 26), see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32229)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32229&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Board of Directors of the Exim Bank referred to in section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) "Development Bank" means the Industrial Development Bank of India established under the`
  line `Industrial Development Bank of India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964);`
  line
  line `(c) "Exim Bank" means the Export-Import Bank of India established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "export" and "import" mean, respectively, export from or import into India or any other`
  line `country of goods or services, or both;`
  line
  line `(e) "goods" includes all materials, commodities and articles in a solid, liquid or gaseous state and`
  line `all forms of energy;`
  line
  line `(f) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(i) "scheduled bank" means a bank, for the time being, included in the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(j) "services" includes,--`
  line
  line `(I) providing personnel (including skilled or unskilled workmen and persons for rendering`
  line `technical or other services) for the purposes of any work or project (by whatever name called) or`
  line `any activity;`
  line
  line `(II) transferring of technology, including transferring, or securing the transfer of rights,`
  line `knowhow, expertises or other skill with respect to any patent, invention, model, design, secret`
  line `formula or process or similar property;`
  line
  line `(III) furnishing any information, blueprints, plans, or advice with respect to any matter; and`
  line
  line `(IV) making available any other resources.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32230)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Export-Import Bank of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32230&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such`
  line `date as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint, there shall be established for the purposes`
  line `of this Act a corporation to be known as the Export-Import Bank of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Exim Bank shall be a body corporate with the name aforesaid having perpetual succession`
  line `and a common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property and to contract, and may, by that name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Exim Bank shall be at Bombay or at such other place as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(4) The Exim Bank may establish offices, branches or agencies at such places in or outside India as it`
  line `may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32231)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Authorised capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 2012, s. 2, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32231&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The authorised capital of the Exim Bank shall be ten thousand crores of`
  line `rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, increase the said capital up to an amount`
  line `that it may deem necessary from time to time.]`
  line
  line `(2) The issued capital of the Exim Bank shall be wholly subscribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32232)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Management.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32232&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs and`
  line `business of the Exim Bank shall vest in the Board, which may exercise all powers and do all acts and`
  line `things which may be exercised or done by the Exim Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in the regulations made under this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) the chairman, if he is a whole-time director or if he is holding offices both as the chairman and`
  line `the managing director, or`
  line
  line `(b) the managing director, if the chairman is not a whole-time director, or, if the chairman being a`
  line `whole-time director, is absent,`
  line
  line `shall also have powers of general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs and business`
  line `of the Exim Bank and may also exercise all powers and do all acts and things which may be exercised or`
  line `done by the Exim Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board in discharging its functions shall act on business`
  line `principles with due regard to public interest.`
  line
  line `(4) In the discharge of its functions under this Act, the Exim Bank shall be guided by such directions`
  line `in matters of policy involving public interest as the Central Government may give to it in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32233)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Constitution of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32233&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Directors of the Exim Bank shall consist of the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a chairman and a managing director appointed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the same person may be appointed to function both as chairman and as managing`
  line director;
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(aa) two whole-time directors appointed by the Central Government;]`
  line
  line `(b) one director nominated by the Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `(c) one director nominated by the Development Bank;`
  line
  line `(d) one director nominated by the Export Credit and Guarantee Corporation Limited, being a`
  line `Government Company within the meaning of section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(e) not more than twelve directors nominated by the Central Government of whom--`
  line
  line `(i) five directors shall be officials of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) not more than three directors shall be from the scheduled banks;`
  line
  line `(iii) not more than four directors shall be persons who have special knowledge of, or`
  line `professional experience in, export or import or financing thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The chairman and the managing director ^2`
  line `[or the whole-time director] shall hold office for such`
  line `term, not exceeding ^3`
  line `[five years], as the Central Government may specify in this behalf and any person so`
  line `appointed shall be eligible for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government shall have the`
  line `right to terminate the term of office of the chairman or the managing director, ^2`
  line `[or the whole-time`
  line `director] as the case may be, at any time before the expiry of the term specified under sub-section (2), by`
  line `giving him notice of not less than three months in writing or three months’ salary and allowances in lieu`
  line `thereof, and the chairman or the managing director, ^2`
  line `[or the whole-time director] as the case may be, shall`
  line `also have the right to relinquish his office at any time before the expiry of the term specified under`
  line `sub-section (2) by giving to the Central Government notice of not less than three months in writing or`
  line `three months’ salary and allowances in lieu thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) The chairman and the managing director ^2`
  line `[or the whole-time director] shall receive such salary`
  line `and allowances as may be determined by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, at any time, remove the chairman or the managing director,`
  line ^2
  line `[or the whole-time director] as the case may be, from office:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be removed from his office under this sub-section unless he has been`
  line `given an opportunity of showing cause against his removal.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(6) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (7), any director nominated under clause (b)`
  line `or clause (c) or clause (d) or clause (e) of sub-section (1) and not being an official of Government or not`
  line `being a whole-time director or official of the Reserve Bank or the Development Bank or the said Export`
  line `Credit and Guarantee Corporation Limited or a scheduled bank, shall hold office for such term, not`
  line `exceeding three years, as the Central Government or, as the case may be, the authority nominating him,`
  line `may specify in this behalf ^5`
  line `***, and shall be eligible for re-nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such director shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding six years.]`
  line
  line `(7) Any ^6`
  line `***director nominated under this section shall hold office during the pleasure of the`
  line `authority nominating him.`
  line
  line `(8) The Board shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard`
  line `to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) The chairman or, if for any reason he is unable to attend a meeting of the Board, the managing`
  line `director ^2`
  line `[or the whole-time director] or, in the event of both the chairman and the managing director ^2`
  line [or
  line `the whole-time director] being unable to attend a meeting, any other director nominated by the chairman in this behalf and in the absence of such nomination any director elected by the directors present from`
  line `among themselves, shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(10) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `votes of the directors present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the chairman, or in his`
  line `absence, the managing director, ^7`
  line `[or the whole-time director] or in the absence of both the chairman and`
  line `the managing director, ^7`
  line `[or the whole-time director] the person presiding, shall have and exercise a`
  line `second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(11) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (10), every director of the Board shall have one vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 2012, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-2-2012)`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 81 of 1985, s. 16, for "three years" (w.e.f. 1-5-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 39, for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `5. The words "and thereafter until his successor enters upon his office" omitted by Act 45 of 2006, s. 18 (w.e.f. 16-10-2006).`
  line
  line `6. The word "other" omitted by Act 66 of 1988, s. 39 (w.e.f 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 11 of 2012, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32234)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Committees.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32234&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may constitute such Committees whether consisting wholly of`
  line `directors or wholly of other persons or partly of directors and partly of other persons for such purpose or`
  line `purposes as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Any Committee constituted under sub-section (1) shall meet at such times and places and shall`
  line `observe such rules or procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meeting as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (32235)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Fees and allowances of directors and members of Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 2012, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32235&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The directors and the members`
  line `of a Committee shall be paid such fees and allowances as may be prescribed for attending the meetings of`
  line `the Board or of any Committee constituted in pursuance of this Act and for attending to any other work of`
  line `the Exim Bank:`
  line /hrt1
  line
  line `Provided that no fees shall be payable to the chairman, if he is appointed as a whole-time chairman,`
  line `or to the managing director ^1`
  line `[or the whole-time director] or to any other director or member who is an`
  line `official of the Government, the Reserve Bank or the Development Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (32236)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Disqualifications.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32236&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be a director of the Board constituted under this Act, who--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or at any time has been, adjudged insolvent, or`
  line
  line `(b) is of unsound mind and has been so declared by a competent court, or`
  line
  line `(c) is, or has been, convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `involves moral turpitude, or`
  line
  line `(d) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, so abused his position as a director, as to`
  line `render his continuance on the Board detrimental to the interests of the general public, or`
  line
  line `(e) has been, for any reason, removed from the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (32237)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Business of Exim Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32237&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Exim Bank may grant in or outside India loans and advances`
  line `by itself or in participation with any bank or financial institution whether in or outside India for the`
  line `purposes of export or import and shall also function as the principal financial institution for co-ordinating`
  line `the working of institutions engaged in financing of the export and import in such manner as it may deem`
  line appropriate.
  line
  line `(2) The Exim Bank may also carry on and transact all or any of the following kinds of business,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) granting loans and advances to a scheduled bank or any other bank or financial institution`
  line `notified in the Official Gazette by the Central Government in this behalf by way of refinance of loans`
  line `and advances granted by it for purpose of export or import;`
  line
  line `(b) underwriting the issue of stocks, shares, bonds or debentures of any company engaged in`
  line `export or import;`
  line
  line `(c) issuing bid bonds or guarantees in or outside India by itself or in participation with any`
  line `government, bank or financial institution in or outside India;`
  line
  line `(d) accepting, collecting, discounting, re-discounting, purchasing, selling or negotiating in or`
  line `outside India, bills of exchange or promissory notes arising out of transactions relating to export or`
  line `import and granting of loans and advances in or outside India against such bills or promissory notes;`
  line
  line `(e) granting, opening, issuing, confirming or endorsing letters of credit and negotiating or`
  line `collecting bills and other documents drawn thereunder;`
  line
  line `(f) undertaking any transaction involving a combination of government to government and`
  line `commercial credit for purposes of export or import;`
  line
  line `(g) granting lines of credit to the government of any foreign State or any financial institution or`
  line `person outside India for purposes of export or import;`
  line
  line `(h) granting loans and advances outside India for any Indian joint venture;`
  line
  line `(i) granting loans and advances to any person in India in connection with his equity contribution`
  line `in any joint venture in any country outside India;`
  line
  line `(j) financing export or import of machinery and equipment on lease basis;`
  line
  line `(k) subscribing to, or investing in, or purchasing of, stocks, shares, bonds or debentures of any`
  line `development bank or Export-Import Bank of any country outside India;`
  line
  line `(l) buying or selling of, or entering into such other dealings in, foreign exchange, as may be`
  line `necessary for the discharge of its functions;`
  line
  line `(m) opening of any account in any bank in or outside India or the making of any agency`
  line `arrangement with, or acting as an agent or correspondent of, any bank or other institution in or outside`
  line India;
  line
  line `(n) transferring, for consideration, any instrument relating to loans and advances granted by it;`
  line
  line `(o) issuing participation certificates;`
  line
  line `(p) subscribing to, or investing in, or purchasing of stocks, shares, bonds or debentures to the`
  line `extent necessary for the enforcement of a lien, pledge or other contractual right;`
  line
  line `(q) undertaking and financing of research, surveys, techno-economic or any other study in`
  line `connection with the promotion and development of international trade;`
  line
  line `(r) providing technical, administrative and financial assistance of any kind for export or import;`
  line
  line `(s) planning, promoting, developing and financing export-oriented concerns;`
  line
  line `(t) forming or conducting subsidiaries for carrying out its functions;`
  line
  line `(u) acting as agent of the Central Government, any State Government, the Reserve Bank, the`
  line `Development Bank or any other person as the Central Government may authorise;`
  line
  line `(v) collecting, compiling and disseminating market and credit information in respect of`
  line `international trade;`
  line
  line `(w) doing any other kind of business which the Central Government may authorise;`
  line
  line `(x) generally doing such other acts and things as may be incidental to, or consequential upon, the`
  line `exercise of its powers or the discharge of its duties under this Act or any other law for the time being`
  line `in force, including sale or transfer of any of its assets.`
  line
  line `(3) The Exim Bank may receive in consideration of any of the services mentioned in`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2) such commission, brokerage, interest, remuneration or fees as may be agreed`
  line upon.
  line
  line `(4) The Exim Bank shall not grant any loan or advance or other financial accommodation on the`
  line `security of its own bonds or debentures.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (32238)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Loans by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32238&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, advance to the Exim Bank--`
  line
  line `(a) a loan of twenty crores of rupees at a rate of interest of five and a quarter per cent. per annum`
  line `repayable in fifteen equal annual instalments, commencing on the expiry of a period of fifteen years`
  line `from the date of receipt of the loan; and`
  line
  line `(b) such further sums of money by way of loan on such terms and conditions as may be agreed`
  line `upon:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, on a request being made to it by the Exim Bank,`
  line `increase the number of instalments or alter the amount of any instalment or vary the date on which`
  line `any instalment is payable under clause (a).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (32239)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Borrowings and acceptance of deposits by Exim Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32239&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Exim Bank may, for the`
  line `purposes of carrying out its functions under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) issue and sell bonds and debentures with or without the guarantee of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) borrow money from the Reserve Bank--`
  line
  line `(i) repayable on demand or on the expiry of fixed periods not exceeding ninety days from the`
  line `date on which the money is so borrowed against the security of stocks, funds and securities (other`
  line `than immovable property) in which a trustee is authorised to invest trust money by any law for`
  line `the time being in force in India;`
  line
  line `(ii) against bills of exchange or promissory notes arising out of bona fide commercial or trade`
  line `transactions and bearing two or more good signatures and maturing within five years from the`
  line `date of the borrowing;`
  line
  line `(iii) out of the National Industrial Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund established under`
  line `section 46C of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) for any of the purposes specified`
  line `in that section;`
  line
  line `(c) borrow money from such other authority, organisation or institution in India as may generally`
  line `or specially be approved by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) accept deposits repayable after the expiry of a period which shall not be less than twelve`
  line `months from the date of the making of the deposit on such terms as may generally or specially be`
  line `approved by the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, on a request being made to it by the Exim Bank, guarantee the`
  line `bonds and debentures issued by that Bank as to the repayment of principal and the payment of interest at`
  line `such rate as may be fixed by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (32240)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Loans in foreign currency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32240&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973) or in any other law for the time being in force relating to foreign`
  line `exchange, the Exim Bank may, for the purpose of granting loans and advances under this Act, borrow,`
  line `with the previous consent of the Central Government, foreign currency from any foreign State or from`
  line `any bank or financial institution in any foreign country or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (32241)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Grants, donations, etc., to Exim Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32241&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Exim Bank may receive gifts, grants, donations or`
  line `benefactions from Government or any other source in or outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (32242)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Export Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32242&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `With effect from such date as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, appoint, the Exim Bank shall establish a special fund to be called the Export Development`
  line Fund.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (32243)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Credits to Export Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32243&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `To the Export Development Fund shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all amounts received for the purposes of that Fund by way of loans, gifts, grants, donations or`
  line `benefactions from Government or any other source in or outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) repayments or recoveries in respect of loans, advances or other facilities granted from the`
  line Fund;
  line
  line `(c) income or profits from investments made from the Fund; and`
  line
  line `(d) income accruing or arising to the Fund by way of interest or otherwise, on account of the`
  line `application of the Fund in accordance with the provisions of section 17.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (32244)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Utilisation of Export Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32244&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Exim Bank considers it necessary or`
  line `desirable so to do, it may, subject to the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3), disburse or spend from the`
  line `Export Development Fund any amount on account or in consequence of the grant of any loan or advance,`
  line `or on account or in consequence of entering into any arrangement under sub-section (1) or clause (b) or`
  line `clause (c) or clause (d) or clause (q) or clause (r) or clause (s) or clause (w) or clause (x) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 10:`
  line
  line `Provided that before granting any such loan or advance or entering into any such arrangement, the`
  line `Exim Bank shall obtain the prior approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Before seeking the approval of the Central Government under sub-section (1), the Exim Bank`
  line `shall satisfy itself that banking or other financial institutions or other agencies are not likely to grant such`
  line `loan or advance, or to enter into any such arrangement in the ordinary course of business.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall, before giving its approval, satisfy itself that such loan, advance or`
  line `arrangement is necessary as a matter of priority in the interests of the international trade of the country.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing contained in this section shall be`
  line `deemed to preclude the Exim Bank from granting any loan or advance or from entering into any`
  line `arrangement under sub-section (1) or clause (b) or clause (c) or clause (d) or clause (q) or clause (r) or`
  line `clause (s) or clause (w) or clause (x) of sub-section (2) of section 10 without the approval of the Central`
  line `Government, if no amount in respect thereof is to be disbursed or spent from the Export Development`
  line Fund.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (32245)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Debits to Export Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32245&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) To the Export Development Fund shall be debited--`
  line
  line `(a) such amounts as may from time to time be disbursed or spent under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(b) such amounts as may be required for discharging the liabilities in respect of loans received for`
  line `the purposes of that Fund;`
  line
  line `(c) any loss arising on account of investment made out of that Fund; and`
  line
  line `(d) such expenditure arising out of, or in connection with, the administration and application of`
  line `the Fund as may be determined by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) No amount shall be debited to the Export Development Fund except as provided for in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (32246)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Accounts and audit of Export Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32246&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The balance-sheet and accounts of the`
  line `Export Development Fund shall be prepared in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall cause the books and accounts of the Export Development Fund to be closed and`
  line `balanced as on the 31st day of December each year .`
  line
  line `(3) The Export Development Fund shall be audited by one or more auditors appointed by the Central`
  line `Government under section 24 who shall make a separate report thereon.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (2), (3), (4) and (6) of section 24 shall, so far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to the audit of the Export Development Fund.`
  line
  line `(5) The Exim Bank shall furnish to the Central Government, within four months from the date on`
  line `which the accounts of the Export Development Fund are closed and balanced, a copy of the balance-sheet`
  line `and accounts together with a copy of the auditors' report and a report on the operation of the Fund during`
  line `the relevant year and the Central Government shall, as soon as may be after they are received by it, cause`
  line `the same to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (32247)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Liquidation of Export Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32247&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Export Development Fund shall not be closed`
  line `or wound up save by order of the Central Government and in such manner as that Government may`
  line direct.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (32248)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `General Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32248&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `All receipts of the Exim Bank other than those which are to be credited to the`
  line `Export Development Fund under this Act shall be credited to a Fund to be called the General Fund and all`
  line `payments by the Exim Bank, other than those which are to be debited to the Export Development Fund,`
  line `shall be made out of the General Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (32249)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Preparation of accounts and balance-sheet.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32249&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The balance-sheet and accounts of the Exim`
  line `Bank shall be prepared in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall cause the books and accounts of the Exim Bank to be closed and balanced as on`
  line `the 31st day of December each year.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (32250)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Disposal of Profits accruing to General Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32250&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Exim Bank may establish a Reserve`
  line `Fund to which may be transferred such sums as that Bank may deem fit out of the annual profits accruing`
  line `to the General Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) After making provision for bad and doubtful debts, depreciation of assets and for all other matters`
  line `for which provision is necessary or expedient or which is usually provided for by bankers and for the`
  line `Reserve Fund referred to in sub-section (1), the Exim Bank shall transfer the balance of the net profits to`
  line `the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (32251)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32251&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accounts of the Exim Bank shall be audited by auditors duly qualified to act as`
  line `auditors under sub-section (1) of section 266 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), who shall be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government for such term and on such remuneration as the Central Government`
  line `may fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The auditors shall be supplied with a copy of the annual balance-sheet of the Exim Bank and it`
  line `shall be their duty to examine it together with the accounts and vouchers relating thereto and they shall`
  line `have a list delivered to them of all books kept by the Exim Bank and shall at all reasonable times have`
  line `access to the books accounts, vouchers and other documents of the Exim Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) The auditors may, in relation to such accounts, examine any director or any officer or other`
  line `employee of the Exim Bank and shall be entitled to require from the Board or officer or other employee`
  line `of the Exim Bank such information and explanation as they may think necessary for the performance of`
  line `their duties.`
  line
  line `(4) The auditors shall make a report to the Exim Bank upon the annual balance-sheet and accounts`
  line `examined by them and in every such report they shall state whether in their opinion the balance-sheet is a`
  line `full and fair balance-sheet containing all necessary particulars and properly drawn up so as to exhibit a`
  line `true and fair view of the state of affairs of the Exim Bank and in case they had called for any explanation`
  line `or information from the Board or any officer or other employee of the Exim Bank whether it has been`
  line `given and whether it is satisfactory.`
  line
  line `(5) The Exim Bank shall furnish to the Central Government within four months from the date on`
  line `which its accounts are closed and balanced, a copy of its balance-sheet and accounts together with a copy`
  line `of the auditors report and a report of the working of the Exim Bank during the relevant year, and the`
  line `Central Government shall, as soon as may be, after they are received by it, cause the same to be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(6) Without prejudice to anything contained in the preceding sub-sections, the Central Government`
  line `may, at any time, appoint the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India to examine and report upon the`
  line `accounts of the Exim Bank and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such examination and`
  line `report shall be payable by the Exim Bank to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (32252)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32252&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (4) of section 19, nothing contained in this`
  line `Chapter shall apply to the Export Development Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (32253)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Transfer of part of business of Development Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32253&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) On such date as that Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint, all business, property, assets and liabilities, rights, interests,`
  line `privileges and obligations of whatever nature of the Development Bank in so far as they relate to the`
  line `export financing functions of that Bank shall stand transferred to, and vest in, the Exim Bank.`
  line
  line `(2) For the transfer to, and vesting in, the Exim Bank under sub-section (1), the Exim Bank shall pay`
  line `to the Development Bank such amount in such manner and in such number of instalments as may be`
  line `determined by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) All contracts, deeds, bonds, agreements, powers-of-attorney, grants of legal representation and`
  line `other instruments of whatever nature of the Development Bank which relate to the export financing`
  line `functions of that Bank and which are subsisting or having effect immediately before the date referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) and to which the said Bank is a party or which are in favour of that Bank shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if they relate exclusively to the export financing functions of that Bank, be of full force and`
  line `effect against or in favour of the Exim Bank, as the case may be, and may be enforced and acted upon`
  line `as fully and effectively as if instead of the Development Bank the Exim Bank had been a party thereto`
  line `or as if they had been issued in favour of the Exim Bank; and`
  line
  line `(b) if they relate not only to the export financing function of the Development Bank but also to`
  line `any of the other functions of that Bank, be of full force and effect against or in favour of both the`
  line `Development Bank and the Exim Bank and may be enforced or acted upon as fully and effectively as`
  line `if in addition to the Development Bank the Exim Bank had also been a party thereto or as if they had`
  line `been issued in favour of the Development Bank and also the Exim Bank.`
  line
  line `(4) If, on the date referred to in sub-section (1), any suit, appeal or other legal proceeding of whatever`
  line `nature relating to the export financing functions of the Development Bank is pending, the same shall not`
  line `abate, be discontinued or be in any way prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer to the Exim Bank`
  line `of the business of the Development Bank or of anything contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other`
  line `proceeding may,--`
  line
  line `(a) where it relates exclusively to the export financing functions of the Development Bank, be`
  line `continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the Exim Bank; and`
  line
  line `(b) where it relates not only to the export financing functions of the Development Bank but also to`
  line `any of the other functions of that Bank, be continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the`
  line `Development Bank and the Exim Bank or, if the Central Government by special order in writing so`
  line `directs, by or against such one of the said two Banks, as may be specified in such order.`
  line
  line `(5) If any question arises as to whether any contract, deed, bond, agreement, powers-of-attorney,`
  line `grant of legal representation or other instrument referred to in sub-section (3) or any suit, appeal or other`
  line `legal proceeding referred to in sub-section (4) relates or relates exclusively to the export financing`
  line `functions of the Development Bank, it shall be referred to the Central Government for decision and the`
  line `decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of this section shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Industrial Development Bank of India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964) or any other law or any instrument having`
  line `force by virtue of the said Act or other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (32254)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Staff of Exim Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32254&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Exim Bank may appoint such number of officers and other`
  line `employees as it considers necessary or desirable for the efficient performance of its functions and`
  line `determine the terms and conditions of their appointment and service.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the Exim Bank to`
  line `utilise, and for the Development Bank to make available the services of, such staff of the Development`
  line `Bank having experience relating to export financing functions on such terms and conditions as may be`
  line `agreed upon between the Exim Bank and the Development Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) The duties and conduct, terms and conditions of service and the establishment and maintenance of`
  line `a Provident Fund or any other Fund for the benefit of the officers and other employees of the Exim Bank`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (32255)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32255&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, be general or special order, delegate to any director or`
  line `any officer or other employee of the Exim Bank, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may`
  line `be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions under this Act as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (32256)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32256&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Exim Bank shall furnish, from time to time, to the Central Government such`
  line `returns as the Central Government may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (32257)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Obligation as to fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2005, s. 34 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 14-12-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32257&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Exim Bank shall not, except as otherwise`
  line `required by this Act or any other law, divulge any information relating to, or to the affairs, of, its`
  line `constituents except in circumstances in which it is, in accordance with the law or practice and usage`
  line `customary among bankers, necessary or appropriate for the Exim Bank to divulge such information.`
  line
  line `(2) The Exim Bank may, for the purpose of efficient discharge of its functions under this Act, collect`
  line `from, or furnish to, the Central Government, the Development Bank or any scheduled bank or such other`
  line `financial institution, as may be notified in the Official Gazette by the Central Government in this behalf,`
  line `credit information or other information as it may consider useful for the purpose, in such manner and at`
  line `such times, as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section, the expression "credit information" shall have the`
  line `same meaning as in clause (c) of section 45A of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), subject`
  line `to the modification that "banking company" referred to therein shall mean the Development Bank, any`
  line `scheduled bank or other financial institution as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) Every director, member of a committee, auditor or officer or other employee of the Exim Bank or`
  line `of the Development Bank whose services are utilised by the Exim Bank under the provisions of this Act,`
  line `shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and secrecy in the form set out in the`
  line `First Schedule.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[4) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to the credit information disclosed under the Credit`
  line `Information Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (32258)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Defects in appointments not to invalidate acts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32258&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act or proceeding of the Board or`
  line `of any committee of the Exim Bank shall be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Board or the committee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) No act done by any person acting in good faith as a director shall be deemed to be invalid merely`
  line `on the ground that he was disqualified to be a director or that there was any other defect in his`
  line appointment.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (32259)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Arrangement with Exim Bank on appointment of directors to prevail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32259&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any`
  line `arrangement entered into by the Exim Bank with a company provides for the appointment by the Exim`
  line `Bank of one or more directors of such company, such provisions and any appointment of directors made`
  line `in pursuance thereof shall be valid and effective notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or in any other law for the time being in force or in the memorandum,`
  line `articles of association or any other instrument relating to the company, and any provision regarding share`
  line `qualification, age-limit, number of directorships, removal from office of directors and such like conditions`
  line `contained in any such law or instrument aforesaid, shall not apply to any director appointed by the Exim`
  line `Bank in pursuance of the arrangement as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) Any director appointed as aforesaid shall--`
  line
  line `(a) hold office during the pleasure of the Exim Bank and may be removed or substituted by any`
  line `person by order in writing of the Exim Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) not incur any obligation or liability by reason only of his being a director or for anything done`
  line `or omitted to be done in good faith in the discharge of his duties as a director or anything in relation`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(c) not be liable to retirement by rotation and shall not be taken into account for computing the`
  line `number of directors liable to such retirement.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (32260)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Indemnity of directors`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32260&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every director shall be indemnified by the Exim Bank against all`
  line `losses and expenses incurred by him, in, or in relation to, the discharge of his duties, except such as are`
  line `caused by his own wilful act or default.`
  line
  line `(2) A director shall not be responsible for any other director or for any officer or other employees of`
  line `the Exim Bank or for any loss or expenses resulting to the Exim Bank from the insufficiency or`
  line `deficiency of the value of, or title to, any property or security acquired or taken on behalf of the Exim`
  line `Bank or the insolvency or wrongful act of any debtor or any person under obligation to the Exim Bank or`
  line `anything done in good faith in the execution of the duties of his office or in relation thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (39548)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=39548&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Exim Bank or any director or any officer or other employee of the Exim Bank or any other person`
  line `authorised by the Exim Bank to discharge any functions under this Act for any loss or damage caused or`
  line `likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this`
  line `Act or any other law or provision having the force of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (32261)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Act 18 of 1891 to apply in relation to Exim Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32261&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The Bankers' Books Evidence Act, 1891`
  line `shall apply in relation to the Exim Bank as if it were a Bank as defined in section 2 of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (32262)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Section 34A and section 36AD only of Act 10 of 1949 to apply to Exim Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32262&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line Nothing
  line `contained in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949, except section 34A and section 36AD thereof, shall apply`
  line `to the Exim Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (32263)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32263&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `[Act 43 of 1961 and Act 7 of 1964 not to apply to Exim Bank.] Omitted by Finance Act, 1998`
  line `(21 of 1998) s. 117 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (32264)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Liquidation of Exim Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32264&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No provision of any law relating to the winding up of companies`
  line `or corporations shall apply to the Exim Bank and the Exim Bank shall not be placed in liquidation save by`
  line `an order of the Central Government and in such manner as it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (32265)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32265&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, make regulations not inconsistent with this Act to provide for all matters for which`
  line `provision is necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the times and places of the meetings of the Board or of any committee constituted under this`
  line `Act and the procedure to be followed at such meetings including the quorum necessary for the`
  line `transaction of business;`
  line
  line `(b) the fees and allowances that may be paid to the directors and the members of a committee;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner in which the balance-sheets and the account of the Export Development`
  line `Fund and the Exim Bank shall be prepared;`
  line
  line `(d) the duties and conduct, and the terms and conditions of service of the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Exim Bank;`
  line
  line `(e) the establishment and maintenance of provident fund or any other fund for the benefit of the`
  line `officers and other employees of the Exim Bank; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation made by the Board under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (32266)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title REPEALED.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32266&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of certain enactments.]--Rep. by Repealing and Amending Act, 1988 (19 of 1988),`
  line `s. 2, and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 31-3-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (32267)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to remove difficulty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088&sectionId=32267&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00049_198128_1517807326088
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, do anything, not inconsistent with such provisions, for the`
  line `purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiration of three years from the date on which`
  line `this Act receives the assent of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
